HEADWORD: Illume
<hw>Il*lume"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Illumed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Illuming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>illuminer</ets>.
See <er>Illuminate</er>.]</ety> <def>To throw or spread light upon; to
make light or bright; to illuminate; to illumine.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mountain's brow,⟦br⟧
<qex>Illumed</qex> with fluid gold.</q> <rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Illuminable</ent>⟦br⟧
